casebody.data:
First Department,

November, 1941.

(November 7, 1941.) In the Matter of the Application of Kenneth G. Osborn, Petitioner, Respondent, for an Order of Mandamus against S. Howard Cohen and Others, Constituting the Board of Elections in the City of New York, Respondents, and Samuel W. Phillips, Appellant.

Order unanimously reversed and the application denied. No opinion. Present — Martin, P. J., O’Malley, Townley, Dore and Cohn, JJ.
